# Step Flow — Cursor Rules

## Language & Tooling
- All code must be TypeScript. No .js files in /src.
- Use React functional components with hooks only. No class components.
- Use Zustand for all shared/global state. No Redux, no Context for data state.
- Use Tailwind CSS for layout and spacing. Use custom CSS modules for pixel-art aesthetics, animations, and decorative styling.
- Never use inline styles except for dynamic runtime values (e.g. wheel rotation angle).

## Code Quality
- Write JSDoc comments for all custom hooks and utility functions.
- Always handle loading, error, and empty states in async components.
- Never hardcode user IDs, API keys, or secrets. Always use import.meta.env.
- Type all props with TypeScript interfaces. Never use `any`.
- Import shared types from /src/types/index.ts — never redefine types inline.

## File Conventions
- One component per file. Filename = component name (PascalCase).
- Hooks in /src/hooks/. Utilities in /src/utils/. Stores in /src/store/.
- Co-locate component-specific CSS in a .module.css file next to the component.

## Firebase & API
- All Firestore reads/writes must be scoped to the authenticated userId.
- The Anthropic API key must never appear in client-side code. Use serverless functions only.
- Wrap all Firestore calls in try/catch and surface errors to the UI.

## Accessibility
- All icon-only buttons must have aria-label.
- All modals must trap focus when open.
- Use aria-live regions for timer countdowns and real-time updates.

## Pixel Art Aesthetic
- Use 'Press Start 2P' for headings and game UI text.
- Use 'Nunito' for body text, labels, and form inputs.
- Use the CSS variables defined in src/index.css for all colors — never hardcode hex values.
- Cat sprite animations must use CSS keyframes on spritesheet background-position.
